1.  keep a good reputation<br>
2.  know how to play your class<br>
3.  level to 60.  few guilds turn down lvl 60 warriors that know how to play<br>
4.  make friends in the guild, do exp groups with em<br>
5.  get aa points if you are 60.<br>
6.  try and raid with the one you want in, and dont wipe out their raid.<br>
7.  gear helps your chances since your useable to them immediatly if your gear is decent... but for the most part they'd have to re-equip you anyways.  not that important really.<br>
<br>
they may not be actively seeking warriors, but most guilds could always use extra 60 wars.  sub 60 warriors are mostly useless to raid guilds though <p><a href=http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=7023  target="web">smushums<a</p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/usmushums.showPublicProfile?language=EN>smushums</A> at: 9/11/02 3:31:06 pm<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2F2F4F><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/ucslochraven.showPublicProfile?language=EN>CSLochraven</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>is a Seasoned Veteran</span><br>  Posts: 236<br> <font color=#FF0000>(9/11/02 3:27:57 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthetavern.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1256.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://gs.cdnow.com/graphics/COVERART/local/L/80/01/00138001.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://www.steelwarrior.org/forum/p_ale.gif" align=absmiddle>  Re: How do I get into a raid guild??</span><hr size=1> Getting into raid guilds can be real tough.  I never had any good friends that were uber, so I never had any connections.  Took me a while to finally get in one.<br>
