<br>
I'm an officer and long time member of what we've come to call a &quot;stepping stone guild&quot;  We spend alot of time teaching/learning raiding tactics and farming equipment to better our guild. The most frustrating thing in the world for me is to see a guild mate that I and others have helped over time get to level 60 and say &quot;Well I want to see the high end raid game so I'm gonna join uber_guild_01 instead.. you guys were great.. see ya later&quot; Meenwhile the dedicated few that strive to make our guild a great place to be, as well as capable of reaching higher end content are left with one less member to count on.  So I guess what I'm saying is dont forget the people that got you there. Sure we all want to see new things, but isnt it better when done with old friends? <p><div align="center"><embed width="468" height="148" src="http://www.ameritech.net/users/amplified/SWSig.swf"></div><BR></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/uvelyssa.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Velyssa</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>is a Formidable Opponent</span><br>  Posts: 125<br> <font color=#FF0000>(9/12/02 11:32:02 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthetavern.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1256.topic&index=10>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://www.steelwarrior.org/forum/p_ale.gif" align=absmiddle>  Re: How do I get into a raid guild??</span><hr size=1> /agree<br>
<br>
My guild is not one I would consider &quot;uber&quot; or even a &quot;raiding&quot; guild, only in HoT right now.  BUT, that said, I'd rather see the end game content with them then without them.  Depends on what you play for, I guess.<br>
<br>
I pretty much checked out where i could get in by looking at web sites and guild requirements, and from that list narrowed it down by reputation.  I wanted a guild with a good reputation, that was raiding, but still growing because maybe they'd let me grow with them since I was only 52 and playing my first character.  Then I made a specific point of meeting people from that guild, and generally being &quot;good to have around.&quot;  Actually, I met my sponsor while playing twinks, believe it or not.<br>
<br>
Anyway, everything mentioned is good.  You basically have to &quot;camp&quot; the guild you want.  But first, you have to target which guild you want, imo.  You don't want to be trying to get into 5 guilds at once-it doesn't look good.<br>
<br>
Good luck!<br>
