<br>
On a 'nicer' server, there is more room at the top, thanks to rotations etc, but there's only so many mobs to kill and the guilds that are ahead of you because they already know how to kill those mobs, and they can do it faster and with less people than you can, because they have better gear and they already know the strat.  You might steal one now and then, but you're at a huge disadvantage, and you won't be able to get that kinda stuff reliably until the uber guilds are done with it an moving on to bigger and better things.  Result, you stay where you are as a lower level guild, and your more ambitious members that want to see the high-end game in the next year wind up leaving for a bigger guild.  I always feel bad for people that are genuinely trying to get their guild to the top, but the odds are seriously stacked against them. <p><a href=http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=6629>Brutul Vilesilencer</a><br>

<a href=http://images.allposters.com/images/54/039_15016.jpg>Barbarian</a> Warlord of the <a href=http://www.blackcompany.cc>Black Company</a><br>
<a href=http://www.realpoor.com>Tarew Marr</a></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/uxanhopebringer.showPublicProfile?language=EN>XanHopebringer</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>knows that Warriors are superior</span><br>  Posts: 10<br> <font color=#FF0000>(9/12/02 3:31:09 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthetavern.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1256.topic&index=12>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://www.steelwarrior.org/forum/p_ale.gif" align=absmiddle>  Re: How do I get into a raid guild??</span><hr size=1> Heh, this is the first time I've ever seen this question on a public msgboard like this.  Well... hmmm... You'd first begin by visiting to your server web page/community msgboards to look for a list of guilds.  After you find the guild that best suits your play hours/raid zones/factions etc, you would look at the classes they need.  Usually, they would give you a list of the classes they need from highest priority to lowest.  It usually looks something like this:<br>
<br>
1. Cleric<br>
2. Wizard<br>
3. Rogue<br>
4. Shaman<br>
etc.<br>
etc.<br>
<br>
If you are a 60 warrior, you'll be in the category of &quot;moderate desirability.&quot;  Most of the hardcore raiding guilds already have established main tanks, rampage tanks, etc.   This means that to get into this guild, you would have to put in a huge amount of time into AAs. Sometimes your current equipment is a factor, but very rarely. Being level 60 is a no brainer, but having something like 60-100 AA points and ND, CS, CA, PE can probably get you into an evaluation period with the guild where you raid with them for months and months until a tank slot opens up for ya.  This is in contrast to a class that is in &quot;high desirability&quot; like a cleric, who would be snatched up no matter how many AAs he/she has.  A class who is &quot;low desirability&quot; would have to be level 60 with like over 150 AA points, have no life, and play like 24-7.  An example would be... Like... Say... A Shadow Knight.  Necromancers were in that list prior to the DoT stacking change.  Not sure so much now.<br>
<br>
This is basically true for all decent raiding guilds.  The better the guild, the larger the time-sinks you have to put in.  These time-sinks include:<br>
<br>
1. Making friends with dozens of folks in the guild.  This takes a long, long, long time.  It's harder than it sounds.<br>
<br>
2. Leveling up.  The more AAs, the better your chances, depending on where you fit on their &quot;desirability&quot; list.<br>
<br>
3. Going on raids.  This is harder than it sounds.  For a guild that does spur of the moment raids, or are raiding in areas your are unfamiliar with, you might find yourself severely embarassed.  Being at every raid will better your chances, but then again, this is harder than it sounds.  Especially if you are not temporarily tagged and can't join in on their guild discussions.   <p><img src="http://www.geocities.com/dakkan2001/xsigtest1.gif">
</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2F2F4F><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/ufederikoeq.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Federiko EQ</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://eqfederiko.homestead.com/files/icon.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>knows that Warriors are superior</span><br>  Posts: 61<br> <font color=#FF0000>(9/12/02 6:33:36 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthetavern.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1256.topic&index=13>Reply</a>    <br>ezSupporter<br> <BR><img src=http://eqfederiko.homestead.com/files/colorbars.gif WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://www.steelwarrior.org/forum/p_ale.gif" align=absmiddle>  Re: How do I get into a raid guild??</span><hr size=1> I guess my point would be that it's more fun if your character follows the same arc of progression as the game itself.  I think too many characters level to 60 in the sole hope of joining an end game guild, not realizing that they just skipped years of content.  Why?  For better loot.  Is the thrill of killing Dain as a guild for the first time any less exciting than taking out Arch Lich?  Sure you may be a year and half behind the top guild but the accomplishment is still just as great.<br>
<br>
It's entirely possible for a guild to progress in power without being in the top 5.  And if any guild see themselves as a &quot;stepping stone&quot;, then your leadership is doing something wrong or you're recruiting the wrong people.  In a guild of friends, turnover should be minimal.<br>
<br>
To the original poster, follow the advice of everyone else.  I have no authority on the subject.<br>
<br>
