<br>
Usually casual guilds will never be able to be serious raid guilds due to time constraints. Unless a majority of the guild has at least 25~30 hours a week to devote to the game, they won't be able to handle a raiding schedule. Many people have better things to do than play EQ :P<br>
<br>
So ask to join raids, see if you like the style of playing, and then app with them. Don't sweat it too much, it's not rocket science getting into an uber guild.....biggest thing is the time. <p><A HREF="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=37533">Susanoe Orbatos</A> - <A HREF="http://zs.20m.com/">Zenith Sage</A></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/ukailynofpovar.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Kailyn Of Povar</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/image/globalBlack.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>is a Formidable Opponent</span><br>  Posts: 155<br> <font color=#FF0000>(9/13/02 5:18:48 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthetavern.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1256.topic&index=16>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://www.steelwarrior.org/forum/p_ale.gif" align=absmiddle>  Re: How do I get into a raid guild??</span><hr size=1> The other question that has to be asked, is what level of raiding guild are you looking to join? A Triton/FoH/other scary top level guild, or one of the lessor ubers?<br>
